The area you tagged is underlain by gypsum rocks that date back to the Carboniferous Period (~360 to 299 million years ago). Over its 175-year history, the Geological Survey of Canada has studied areas like this to better understand how they came to be. Gypsum is easily dissolved by groundwater, leading to sinkholes like the one found just north of the Trans-Canada Highway in Baddeck. So try not to spill anything. #geostories175
